# Next.js Patterns

## Route Groups

```
src/app/
├── (protected)/    # Requires auth — wraps with Navigation or AdminDashboardLayout
│   ├── layout.tsx  # Auth guard + layout switching
│   ├── dashboard/
│   ├── exam/
│   ├── result/
│   ├── reports/
│   ├── settings/
│   ├── student/
│   └── exams/
├── (public)/       # No auth required
│   ├── login/
│   └── register/
└── page.tsx        # Landing page (login/register/forgot-password form switch)
```

## Layout Hierarchy

1. `app/layout.tsx` — Root: fonts, metadata, `<AppProviders>` (QueryClient + GlobalLoading)
2. `app/(protected)/layout.tsx` — Auth check, renders `AdminDashboardLayout` for admin routes or `Navigation` + children for student routes

## Admin vs Student Shell

```typescript
const ADMIN_ROUTES = ['/dashboard', '/student', '/exams', '/reports', '/settings']
// Admin on admin routes → AdminDashboardLayout (sidebar + header)
// Student or non-admin routes → Navigation bar + content
```

## Adding a New Protected Page

1. Create `src/app/(protected)/my-page/page.tsx`
2. Add `'use client'` directive
3. Wrap content in `<RoleGuard allowedRoles={[...]}>`
4. Add route to `ROLE_PERMISSIONS` in `src/lib/authorization.ts`
5. Add nav link in `src/components/common/Navigation.tsx` if needed

## Client Components

All interactive pages use `'use client'` — hooks (useAuth, useRouter, useState, etc.) require it.
